row.Body: When I've printed an object I've had to choose between high resolution and quick prints. What techniques or technologies can I use or deploy to speed up my high resolution prints?
row.Title: How to obtain high resolution prints in a shorter period of time?

row.Body:
I would like to buy a 3D printer, but I'm concerned about the health risks that are associated with its operation. Some groups of scientists say it can be harmful for humans.

What do I need to consider before buying a 3D printer if I care about my health? Are there any safe printers?
row.Title: Is 3D printing safe for your health?

row.Body: I know the minimum layer height will effect how detailed of an item you can print and the amount of time it takes to print something, but is it necessary to have an extremely low minimum layer height if you plan to print only larger objects?
row.Title: How important is the minimum layer height on a 3d printer?
